<br>
I'll be leading a Fear raid shortly and wanted to get your takes on the break-in. I know this is old stuff, but many in our Guild can still use some PoF drops, and I need to do my Golem for the epic...<br>
<br>
That said, our plan is to do a west wall break. One of our monks will FD at zone in and let us know when the coast is somewhat clear. When ready, two break groups composed mainly of melees, a cleric and a chanter will invis, zone, run left to wall, and fight to the death (and hopefully live). We plan to rinse and repeat until zone-in is somewhat clear for the other groups to zone in. <br>
<br>
The reason I choose this break strategy is because last time I went to PoF, all groups zoned in at about the same time (10 secs apart). What ended up happening is some would lose invis, get attacked, and train their mob to the others who had amassed at the West wall. Of course we gave the obligatory warning to &quot;stand and die&quot;, but someone inevitably screwed that up. This time, with only two break groups (composed of mid to high 50s players), I'm hoping to minimize the trainage.<br>
<br>
Let me know if you think this is a sound strategy, or if you have other suggestions. We will likely have 6-7 groups composed of a large variety of players (from lev 46 to mid and upper 50s).<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance.<br>
Zeg<br>
<br>
<br>
