 <p><IMG SRC="http://home.uchicago.edu/~kgoetz/signature_Z.GIF" ALT="Zego" border=0 ALIGN=CENTER></IMG>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxiththewizard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xith the Wizard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/30/02 12:17:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12207.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear Break Advice</span><hr size=1> The 2 group strategy is what we use when we go in.  We almost never have a death on break unless someone really fooks up.  Generally the parties look like this<br>
<br>
Group 1<br>
Raid MA (Highest most well equipted WARRIOR)<br>
Primary Mezzer (highest chanter)<br>
Primary Healer (highest Cleric)<br>
Epic Rogue<br>
Epic Monk<br>
Wizard (usually me or Tahas)<br>
<br>
Group 2<br>
Raid SA (Second best equipped tank)<br>
Secondary Chanter<br>
Slower (Highest Shaman, preferably with Malo)<br>
Secondary Healer (cleric)<br>
Monk<br>
Wizard (the one that wasnt in group 1)<br>
<br>
This is where things get tricky, Wizards, your not there to nuke on the delicate fear break, your there, with Rune on, standing at Full mana, in case things get ugly.  Your ONLY job on a break is emergency Evac to SRo, so you dont lose people inside, and have a hell of a time getting those corpses back.<br>
<br>
Sometimes you can break it without any evac, some times you take 3 or 4 tries at it.  Just all depends on what the mobs want to do that day, and how many times that first mez gets resisted.<br>
<br>
If either of the chanters go down, you evac, if either of the clerics go down, you evac.  If the Main assist goes down .. SA takes over while MA group cleric Rezzes and rebuffs MA.<br>
<br>
If it looks like its getting messy guys, use your best judgement, and evac your party, they may whine for a minute, but they will understand that you did it to save them.<br>
<br>
Xith N'Shezbenon<br>
Sorcerer<br>
Dark Templars<br>
Xegony<br>
<br>
<br>
