<br>
and always kill imps first, they have massive aggro ranges and usually train mobs with them from nearly the other side of the zone with them <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uquallos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quallos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/30/02 12:00:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12207.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Myself, I prefer the ...</span><hr size=1> My group breaks it like this:<br>
<br>
Group composition:  wizard, enchanter, ranger, cleric, warrior, shaman, all 60.<br>
<br>
1)  Zone in invis, and full mana, stand at entry portal (don't bother running to any wall).<br>
2)  Wizard, Ranger and Warrior beat the 1st aggro mob into the dirt as fast as possible.  Enchanter puts all adds on ice.  Shaman slows all.  Cleric keeps us standing.<br>
3)  Wizard, Ranger and Warrior beat the 2nd mob (chosen by enchanter) into the dirt as fast as possible.<br>
4)  If mana is still good, repeat step 3, otherwise, evac.<br>
5)  Go to step 1.  Repeat the process 3 or 4 times until you're getting so few adds at the portal that you can keep the pace up without evacing.<br>
6)  The plane is broken<br>
<br>
We've done this several times.<br>
Advantages<br>
 -  its fun<br>
 -  nobody dies<br>
 -  its relaxing to go &quot;commando&quot; with a single group, rather than be shouting raid-style instructions to a mob of people<br>
<br>
Disadvantages<br>
 -  the break takes about an hour, as opposed to 30 min with a larger group.<br>
<br>
<br>
cheers, <p><font size=+1 color="881133"><b>Quallos</b></font><BR>
Sorcerer<BR>
Bristlebane<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usummarbriseis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Summar Briseis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/30/02 12:39:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12207.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Myself, I prefer the ...</span><hr size=1> Hail Zego! Hope all is well in your World!<br>
<br>
Pretty good advice here the only thing I would add is Mob count. Make sure someone gives an updated mob count on adds so you know what youre facing. I do disagree with Xith on not nuking, I nuke a bit on each mob to speed things up, then hit with concussion and med. Though I wouldnt sit if below 55 which seems to be the break point on agro for medding. Do not let anyone sit to med until broken. Especially if they are under 55, probably not at all if they dont really have a bunch of experience with it !! Once you get most of the wanderers done and get to the end then its time to burn a few. But he is right on making sure each group has an evacer though I prefer to have one person responsible for the call so all groups leave together.<br>
<br>
