 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uscylth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scylth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/30/02 12:59:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12207.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> fear</span><hr size=1> Use an ae group to break fear, cleric, enchanter, 3 wizards, puller.  Zone in, run to west wall.  Enchanter chain stuns, wait, wait, nuke them all.  Send puller back out for more and repeat. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utanstaafl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanstaafl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/30/02 1:18:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12207.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear Break Advice</span><hr size=1> We use a single group portal break.<br>
<br>
Break group - <br>
<br>
Best equiped warrior <br>
highest level monk <br>
highest level enchanter <br>
best cleric <br>
best druid (walking back from Ferrott rings is closer than SRo)<br>
Highest level shaman (or a bard if ones avail)<br>
<br>
Also necessary is an SK and/or second monk.  This person is known as the &quot;Engineer&quot; - a sacrificial lamb that is going to pull the train that clears the path for the break in group to get to the west wall spot near the portal where we initially start our raids from.<br>
<br>
Basically when all are buffed and ready the &quot;Engineer&quot; (solo monk or SK) goes in turns left and runs a short distance down the hill toward the zone wall then FDs.  He then judges pathing and decides when he wants to go.  He calls a be ready and pulls the train as he tells the others to zone in.  <br>
<br>
The break group zones in turns left and runs down the hill toward to the zone wall and gets to work.  IF theings get outta control the druid evacs and we rinse and repeat.<br>
<br>
If a piece of class aromor drops before the break group has a clear path from the portal to the wall then a call is sent out and who gets it is determined by raid rules.  That person then makes a solo run to the loot BUT only when the break group says go.  And they must understand that under NO circumstances do they train the break group.  If they get agro jsut die and we'll drag and rez them. <br>
<br>
It was a little rough getting this style down at first but now we get the full raid complement in zone alive and buffed no more than 30 minutes or so after we start. <br>
<br>
MAKE SURE people can follow directions.  More than once we've had a person zone in turn right (instead of left) and run behind the portal.  This has invariably agro'd a mob or 10 and resulted in a wipeout and long CR - these people don't get invited to future raids of ours (we put a FD monk on the hill to watch for this) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzegomandelbrot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zego Mandelbrot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/30/02 1:23:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12207.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Questions</span><hr size=1> Thanks to everyone for the help. Some really good ideas being offered here. Based on your feedback, the options are:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> * Have a Monk amass a big kite of wanderers to clear the zone-in.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Seems risky. Anyone else do this before? We do have an epic 59 Monk coming along though...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> * Use an AoE group and nuke our way in</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
As much as I would love to do this, we frankly don't have the necessary AoE experience to be successful.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> * Two or three group west wall break (with evacers in case of wipe-out)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Like this idea, but the third group would not be as strong as the other two. Why go to West Wall anyways instead of just fighting at portal?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> * Two or three group portal break (with evacers in case of wipe-out)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I also like this idea, and since you don't go anywhere, there's less chance of attracting additional aggro.. right?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> * Invis, run like mad to NW wall, camp out until clear</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
This is probably my 3rd favorite option. With 7 groups, some idiot will train everyone else... I can just sense it.<br>
<br>
Any other comments?<br>
<br>
Thanks!<br>
Zeg<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulenaddaranatar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenaddar Anatar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/30/02 1:46:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12207.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions</span><hr size=1> Zego;<br>
<br>
Pretty much tried them all. What I either forgot or didn't notice is the average level of the folks your bringing along with you?<br>
<br>
Sounds like most of your raid is fairly inexperienced. I would sorely try to find atleast one other monk with heavy pulling experience in Fear. No ifs, ands or buts about it. <br>
<br>
Given the inclination that most of you don't have much experience in Fear I would have the monks simply do the &quot;run around the mound&quot; technique and have everyone else simply ensure that the or atleast one cleric gets to the safe spot at the NW corner. Rogues, Monks and even SKs can pull corpses to them. The cleric must camp out ASAP when arriving. <br>
<br>
Yes, someone will dedicate themselves to ruining the raid by running either to the cleric in desparate attempt to live a few seconds longer or better yet, become completely disorientated and run deeper into the zone. Seen it before.<br>
<br>
Don't remember the exact route but if you run straight north to the Firewall then follow the wall up to the corner thats generally regarded as the safest route. Hold back and wait for and roaming scarlings (Imps) to wander back to there pathing away from the firewall if they are there. <br>
<br>
Done this many times and it does work. Not saying that some of the other suggestions won't but this is my best advice for those who don't have tons of Fear exp.<br>
<br>
